hives    Finding Aids    Rare Books    Maps & GIS    Digital Images    Using Special Collections & University Archives    Special Collections Research Guides       Eyebrow menu    Contact Us    My Accounts    Give to the Library    COVID-19    UIC menu    UIC.edu    Campus Map    UIC Today     Toggle Search                  Breadcrumbs    Home    Help     Reserve a study room   Study rooms are available at all libraries.      Chicago  Reserve study rooms online  Daley Library   IDEA Commons Seminar rooms (1st floor) – for groups of two or more UIC students  Group study rooms (3rd and 4th floor) – for groups of three to six UIC students  SMART rooms (3rd floor) – study rooms with multimedia and interactive whiteboards for groups of three to six UIC students   Graduate students and faculty can apply for a research carrel. Learn more about research carrels and apply online.  LHS-Chicago   SMART rooms – group study rooms with multimedia and interactive whiteboards  Large meeting room – with a capacity of up to 14 people, for group study   Peoria  Four study rooms are available on a first come, first served basis (no reservations are accepted). Faculty can reserve rooms for instruction and testing using Outlook.  Rockford  One study room, one conference room and one seminar room are available on a first come, first served basis (no reservations). Check at the circulation desk for availability.  Urbana  UIC College of Medicine and College of Nursing students are welcome to reserve study rooms at any of the UIUC campus libraries using the online reservation system . Use the drop-down menus at the top of the screen to locate the library and type of room that best meets your needs.      How Do I...?     Reserve a research carrel at Daley Library    Can I eat or drink in the library?     Get More Help        Filter by Location    Chicago-Daley    Chicago-Health Sciences    Peoria-Health Sciences    Rockford-Health Sciences    Urbana-Health Sciences      Filter by Topic    Acc